/*!
\page Tpetra_Lesson06 Tpetra Lesson 06: Custom Operator
\brief Writing a custom subclass of Tpetra::Operator

\section Tpetra_Lesson06_Topics Lesson topics

This lesson shows an example of a custom subclass of Tpetra::Operator.
Tpetra::Operator generalizes the idea of a sparse matrix-vector
product.  While Tpetra::CrsMatrix always represents a sparse matrix, a
Tpetra::Operator is just a function from an input Tpetra::MultiVector
to an output Tpetra::MultiVector.

This example implements a Tpetra::Operator subclass that applies a 1-D
Laplacian with Dirichlet boundary conditions.  It accepts a
communicator and a global number of mesh points.

\section Tpetra_Lesson06_Example Code example

This example shows how to implement a custom Tpetra::Operator.

\include lesson06_custom_operator.cpp

